SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS SPECIFICATION (SRS)
ELECTIVE ALLOCATION SYSTEM
1. INTRODUCTION
1.1 PURPOSE
•	To automate the assignment of subjects based on academic merit (CGPA), student preferences, and basket constraints. It replaces manual processes to ensure transparency and compliance with program rules.

1.2 SCOPE
•	The Elective Allocation System manages the complete lifecycle of elective assignment, including:
•	Importing student and subject data
•	Validating preferences and academic eligibility
•	Performing deterministic merit-based allocation
•	Enforcing basket constraints
•	Generating allocation and vacancy reports
•	The system eliminates manual allocation errors and ensures transparency, fairness, and compliance with institutional academic policies.

1.3 DEFINITIONS AND ACRONYMS
Term	Description
OC	Optional Core subject (mandatory allocation)
CGPA	Cumulative Grade Point Average
Basket	Logical grouping of subjects; only one subject per basket is allotted, even if it an optional core only one subject is allotted from that basket
Multi-Pass Allocation	Iterative allocation process until quota is satisfied
Deterministic Allocation	Same input produces same output

1.4 REFERENCES
•	Institutional Academic Allocation Rules
•	Program-specific elective requirements (e.g., IMTech 6, IMTech 8)

2. OVERALL DESCRIPTION
2.1 PRODUCT PERSPECTIVE
•	The system is a standalone web-based academic tool that interacts with a relational database containing:
•	Student records
•	Subject repositories
•	Preference data
•	It replaces manual spreadsheet-based allocation processes.

2.2 PRODUCT FUNCTIONS
•	The system performs the following major functions:
•	Student preference submission
•	Data validation
•	Merit-based student sorting
•	OC allocation (mandatory phase)
•	Multi-pass elective allocation
•	Seat capacity deduction
•	Basket locking mechanism
•	Allocation report generation
•	Vacancy report generation
•	Report export functionality

2.3 USER CHARACTERISTICS
2.3.1 STUDENT
•	Basic web literacy
•	Must rank all available subjects (1 to n)
•	Can view allocation and vacancy reports
2.3.2 ADMINISTRATOR
•	Basic technical knowledge
